The paper deals with the state estimation problem in smart grid networks, which involves the use of optimization techniques and algorithms to detect and mitigate data injection attacks. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of sparse structures and distributed frameworks, which are relevant to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
